Description: Terra Sigillata wheel-made pottery sherd with a fine glossy red slip. Fine yellow pottery fabric.
Curator's comments: Imperial Roman red slip fine tableware sherd of Eastern Terra Sigillata A ware from Syria, dated c. 20BC-40AD (Hayes 1985, form Atlal 47). Copies Italian Terra Sigillata ware form ITS 17.1 (Ettlinger et al. 1990). Ettlinger, E., Hedinger, B., Hoffmann, B., Kenrick, P. M., Pucci, G., Roth- Rubi, K., Schneider, G., von Schnurbein, S., Wells, C. M. & Zabehlicky- Scheffenegger, S. 1990. Conspectus formarum terrae sigillatae Italico modo confectae. Bonn: Dr. Rudolf Habelt GMBH. Hayes, J. W. 1985. Sigillate Orientali. In Encicliopedia dell 'arte antica, atlate della forme ceramica. II ceramica fine Romana nel bacio Mediterraneo (Tarlo ellenism eprimo imperio), pp. 1-96. Rome.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IF.066) (Phase 3)
